{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5345-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4424"},"text":"§ 4424.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Mechanisms to speed deployment of successful weapon system component or technology prototypes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5346-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Selection of Prototype Project for Production and Rapid Fielding","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"A weapon system component or technology prototype project may be selected by the service acquisition executive of the military department concerned for a follow-on production contract or other transaction without the use of competitive procedures, notwithstanding the requirements of sections 3201 through 3205 of this title, if—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5347-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the follow-on production project addresses a high priority warfighter need or reduces the costs of a weapon system;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5348-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" competitive procedures were used for the selection of parties for participation in the original prototype project;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5349-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the participants in the original prototype project successfully completed the requirements of the project; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a534a-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/a/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a prototype of the system to be procured was demonstrated in a relevant environment.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a534b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Special Transfer Authority","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a534c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of a military department may, as specified in advance by appropriations Acts, transfer funds that remain available for obligation in procurement appropriation accounts of the military department to fund the low-rate initial production of the rapid fielding project until required funding for full-rate production can be submitted and approved through the regular budget process of the Department of Defense.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a534d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The funds transferred under this subsection to fund the low-rate initial production of a rapid fielding project shall be for a period not to exceed two years, the amount for such period may not exceed $50,000,000, and the special transfer authority provided in this subsection may not be used more than once to fund procurement of a particular new or upgraded system.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a534e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/b/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The special transfer authority provided in this subsection is in addition to any other transfer authority available to the Department of Defense.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a534f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s4424/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Notification to Congress","children":[],"tail":".—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"Within 30 days after the service acquisition executive of a military department selects a weapon system component or technology project for a follow-on production contract or other transaction, the service acquisition executive shall notify the congressional defense committees of the selection and provide a brief description of the rapid fielding project.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa7a5350-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328/dA/tVIII/s806/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–328, div. A, title VIII, § 806(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2016-12-23"},"text":"Dec. 23, 2016","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/130/2259"},"text":"130 Stat. 2259","children":[],"tail":", § 2447d; renumbered § 4424 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1851/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1851(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (4), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4272"},"text":"134 Stat. 4272","children":[],"tail":", 4273.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa7a5351-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa7a5352-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idaa7a5353-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2021—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1851/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1851(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2447d"},"text":"section 2447d of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1851/c/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1851(c)(4)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “sections 3201 through 3205” for “section 2304” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idaa7a5354-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idaa7a5355-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2021 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2022-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2022","children":[],"tail":", with additional provisions for delayed implementation and applicability of existing law, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1801/d"},"text":"section 1801(d) of Pub. L. 116–283","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s3001"},"text":"section 3001 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idaa7a5356-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2017-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2017","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/328/s806/a/2"},"text":"section 806(a)(2) of Pub. L. 114–328","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s4421"},"text":"section 4421 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
